    "long_instructions": "# Do This:\r\n\r\n**Refer to Strategy 1 & 3**\r\n\r\n1. **Run and Observe:** Run the code and compare the output to the comments describing what should be happening. Take note of any unexpected behavior.\r\n2. **Discuss:** With a partner, identify what might be causing the issue. Consider what is happening differently than expected. <br>\r\n2. **Use AI Assistance:** Since there is no error message, use the AI Chatbot to help analyze your code and find the bug. Ask the AI for debugging advice or explanations of why the code isn’t behaving as expected. <br>\r\n3. **Modify & Fix the Bug:** Adjust the code to resolve the issue.\r\n\t- **Hint:** Focus on checking the logic of your code rather than just syntax errors!\r\n    \r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: black;\">\r\n<h5><strong>📝 Unit Guide</strong></h5>\r\n\r\nDocument your experience with this debugging strategy:\r\n- What worked? \r\n- What challenges did you face? \r\n- How did this strategy help? \r\n- When might it be most useful in the future?\r\n</div>",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\n\n# create two painter objects\nsusan = Painter()\njoe = Painter()\n\n# turn right by turning left 3x\n# takes an object name as the parameter\ndef turn_right(painter):\n  painter.turn_left()\n  painter.turn_left()\n  painter.turn_left()\n\n# paints a line as it moves\ndef paint_line(painter):\n    painter.move()\n    painter.paint(\"blue\")\n    painter.move()\n\n# object susan will paint the top horizontal grid line\npaint_line(susan)\npaint_line(susan)\npaint_line(susan)\n\n# object joe will turn right and paint the left vertical grid line\nturn_right(joe)\npaint_line(joe)\npaint_line(joe)\npaint_line(joe)\n\n# Expected outcome: the top line of the grid will be painted a solid blue line\n# Expected outcome: the left line of the grid will be painted a solid blue line\n\n\n\n\n\n\n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": true,
          "open": true
        }
      },
      "folders": {
      }
    },
    "teacher_markdown": "Students should use AI Chatbot Assistance (Strategy 3) – Students ask the chatbot to explain logic issues.\r\n\r\nEncourages debugging even if there's no clear syntax error but behavior is unexpected."
  },
